visual_elements.description: Figure 29: A plan view diagram illustrating the minimum dimensions for a carport parking space. It shows a car parked within a rectangular space, with a 'Driveway/parking surface' indicated at the entrance. Dimensions for the width and length of the open space are provided.

Figure 30: Two elevation diagrams illustrating the minimum dimensions for a covered parking space (carport). The top diagram shows a 'Left Side Elevation' with a car parked under a sloped roof supported by columns. The bottom diagram shows a 'Front Elevation' of the same carport, also with a car and sloped roof. Both diagrams include dimensions for height and open space.

Diagram within Fig 29 showing a top-down view of a car within a parking space. It indicates 'One of 2 corner columns' at the top left and bottom left corners of the parking space. The space is open on one side, labeled 'open'.

Top diagram within Fig 30, 'Left Side Elevation', showing a car under a carport. It indicates 'One of 2 corner columns' and 'Bottom roof system'. The roof is sloped. The space is open on the side, with a dimension for the horizontal open space and vertical open space.

Bottom diagram within Fig 30, 'Front Elevation', showing a car under a carport. It indicates 'One of 2 corner columns' and 'Bottom roof system'. The roof is sloped. The space is open at the front, with a dimension for the horizontal open space and vertical open space.
